Defendant Natasha M Najda in court with Attorney Jessica A Klein.  District Attorney's Office Law Intern Grant Scaife appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State files an amended information.  Victim impact statement filed.  Court withdraws no contest plea entered on April 15, 2016 and Defendant is entering a no contest plea to Count #1 on amended information filed today (amending to Class I felony).  Case proceeds to sentencing.  There are no corrections to PSI by parties.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Klein makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:   WITHHELD SENTENCE

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS     ** Transfer alllowed to State of Texas**

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribed/sign releases.
____Inform Agent of all prescriptions
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with: Co-actor or any other individuals listed in complaint (except family members)
____Follow all family court orders and/or juvenile court orders
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 
____No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.


RESTITUTION - (JOINT AND SEVERAL):  $500.00 - to Clifford B. (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)
                                                              $8,285.70 - to Clifford B. (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)
                                                              $7,139.57 - to American Family Insurance (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)

COSTS:  $278.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation)

CONDITION TIME:  90 Days Straight time - STAYED - to be used at agent's discretion
